               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Prerequisites</h3>The text on this page aims to reinforce knowledge of the numbers we use today. Before starting, we suggest studying the following previous pages:</p><p><ul><li><htcite0>: in this first text, we show for people their body symmetry.</li> <li><htcite1>: we introduce the idea of counting using our body.</li> <li><htcite2>: exploring the limitations and the necessity of new tools to count.</li> <li><htcite3>: Presentation of the logic behind the sequence between 0 and 19.</li><li><htcite4>: We study the Tens, along with the <i>Ajawob</i> dynasty that ruled the city of Copán, Honduras.</li></ul></p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "20b14681-88c0-438a-a273-a0902ae5db38",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Our sides are equal",
